{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-6311"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Data processing, hosting and related activities — multi-asset market-data aggregation and hosting"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev4 "6311"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :finance/market-data
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:market-data-integrity :feed-license-compliance :disclosure-tier-compliance]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :marketdata-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics false
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:identity :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MarketData-LLM ⊣ MarketDataGovernor (marketdata.policy, seven checks:
  rbac · tolerance-gate (fat-finger/stale-feed defense) ·
  source-provenance-gate (licensed-operator-feed requires an ACTIVE,
  asset-class-covering feed-license) · licensed-disclosure ·
  confidence-floor · halted-instrument-gate (always escalate, any
  confidence) · correction-requests-never-auto-resolve), langgraph
  StateGraph (marketdata.operation), append-only audit ledger
  (marketdata.store/ledger + append-ledger!). Covers five asset classes
  (equities, FX, commodities, crypto, real-estate indices). A phase 0→3
  staged-autonomy gate (marketdata.phase) sits on top of the governor
  and can only narrow, never widen, what the governor already allowed.
  46 tests / 177 assertions green (`clojure -M:dev:test`), demo
  runnable end-to-end (`clojure -M:dev:run`). This is the market-data
  layer cross-referenced by cloud-itonami-isic-6312's
  portal.marketdata-bridge integration."}
